      • RectangularRegion

        RectangularRegion​(Mosaic mosaic,
                  java.lang.String name,
                  int r0,
                  int c0,
                  int h,
                  int w)
        Constructor, it creates the rectangular region. For this, it checks if its name has the correct length, declares its origin and creates a list with all the coordinates that the region occupies.
        Parameters:
        mosaic - The mosaic that constains the region.
        name - The name of our region.
        r0 - The origin row, the row where the region starts.
        c0 - The origin column, the column where the region starts.
        h - The height of the region.
        w - The width of the region.
